Headquarters Regions: Washington DC Metro Area, East Coast, Southern US
Full Description: At Cohen Health and Performance, we believe that all active people deserve the high quality and individually focused care that is typically only reserved for elite athletes. Our mission is to enhance the lives of individuals who desire to live an active lifestyle by providing elite level physical therapy and performance training. This means that we treat you as an individual, rather than splitting time between 2-3 patients at one time. This helps you to overcome injury and return to performing at your highest level in the least amount of time! Dr. Zachary Cohen founded Cohen Health and Performance in 2016 when he knew that something had to change in the physical therapy world. He began his career working in professional sports, delivering the best possible care to his athletes. He was able to spend as much time as was necessary to get them better and was able to perform the treatment that was essential to get them back on the field as quickly as possible. After leaving the professional sports world, he moved to the DMV and for the first time, worked at a typical in-network physical therapy practice. He became aware of the limitations that health insurance companies place upon them, having to treat 2-3 patients per hour, and he was unable to deliver the care patients needed due to what insurance companies would allow. We believe that the health and goals of our patients are too important for that to be acceptable. At Cohen Health and Performance we refuse to be a run of the mill physical therapy clinic!

Full Description: CollegeTennisOnline.com is committed to promoting college tennis by providing the most comprehensive coverage of college tennis on the Internet. We are dedicated to bring you the latest news in college tennis, feature stories, information and statistics on individual players and schools. CollegeTennisOnline.com, launched on March 18, 2001, has already attracted thousands of tennis players, coaches, college recruits, and fans, with over 3.5 million page views per month.  CollegeTennisOnline.com is a site developed and owned by Local Colorz LLC, founded in May 2000, with the vision of promoting college tennis and its coverage internationally. CollegeTennisOnline.com seeks to create a virtual meeting point for the community of college tennis players, coaches, parents and fans. At its inception, CollegeTennisOnline developed a web-application for the ITA with features including online result entry and computer rankings calculation. This application has greatly reduced the time needed to submit and calculate individual and team rankings, allowing the ITA to redirect their efforts to other important endeavors needed to govern and promote college tennis. In March 2001, LCz published all these results onto CollegeTennisOnline.com, allowing the public to view the database, and creating an “internet repository” of official team and individual results, rankings, and news

Description: Polka is an aggregation and collaboration services for managing health.
Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: Polka is a secure aggregation and collaboration service to help users manage their health, backed by Polka's core technology and the belief that data portability begins with "me."   WHY IT IS IMPORTANT AND COMPELLING Today's complex healthcare system grapples with outdated paper systems and unconnected, diverse IT systems, resulting in a lack of timely, accurate information and collaboration, as well as costly financial and treatment errors in patients' healthcare. All of us deal with difficult, if not impossible, access to our own health information and archaic ways to communicate with our health team. Polka keeps users' health information up-to-date and available anytime, anywhere — whether it's for routine check-ups, daily prescription and supplement tracking, during the critical moment of emergencies, or seamless sharing and communication within users' core team of family, friends, and health professionals.     ABOUT POLKA'S TECHNOLOGY  Polka is a secure, scalable framework that was designed as an encompassing service for the individual, as a person, connecting to the network.  Polka creates every service with the user at the center and data portability top of mind. They believe that the user, or "me," should be centralized because they are the definitive point of control, change, and decision-making.
Industry Groups: Health Care, Internet Services, Media and Entertainment, Mobile, Platforms, Software
